article.headline: Tulane 84, Prairie View 63
article.story: NEW ORLEANS (AP) -- Quincy Davis had 19 points, five rebounds and two blocked shots to lead Tulane to a 84-63 win over Prairie View on Saturday night. Tulane (1-2) used a potent inside game and dominated in the paint, outscoring Prairie View (0-3) by a 48-10 margin in the paint. Davis was 9-of-11 shooting from the floor. Marcus Kinzer added 15 points on 6-of-7 shooting and Vincent Camper had 12 points, six rebounds and seven assists. Ben Benfield came off the bench to score 10 points. The Green Wave hit 33-of-55, or 60 percent, of its shots while holding Prairie View to 21-of-65, or 32 percent, shooting. Tulane also held a 46-32 advantage in rebounding as all 13 players on the roster scored. The Green Wave jumped to a 42-17 lead at halftime and pushed that lead to as many as 31. The Panthers used the long-range game and hit seven second-half 3-pointers to pull within 15 at 76-61 with 2:10 to go. But Vincent Camper knocked down three free throws and Ben Benfield added a pair to make it 81-61 with 1:17 on the clock for Tulane. Oscar Thompson led Prairie View with 16 points.
